#
# =============================================================================
# ðŸš« GIT IGNORE RULES - .gitignore
# =============================================================================
#
# PURPOSE:
# --------
# This file tells Git which files to IGNORE when uploading to GitHub.
# It prevents accidentally committing sensitive data, temporary files,
# and system-generated junk.
#
# WHAT IT DOES:
# -------------
# - Keeps secrets (passwords, API keys) out of GitHub
# - Prevents uploading temporary Python files
# - Ignores IDE configuration files
# - Keeps repository clean and secure
#
# WHY THIS MATTERS:
# -----------------
# Without this file, you might accidentally upload:
# - seen_events.json (your personal event history)
# - .env files (which might contain passwords)
# - Python cache files (useless to others)
#
# WHAT YOU NEED TO CHANGE:
# -------------------------
# Nothing! This file is pre-configured with sensible defaults.
# Just make sure this file exists when you push to GitHub.
#
# =============================================================================

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python
env/
venv/
ENV/

# Local database (keep this private)
seen_events.json

# Secrets (NEVER commit these!)
*.env
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
config.py
*secret*
*password*
*credential*
*.pem
*.key

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
